I first came here about 7 months ago because I heard that the owner of this place was a brother to the owner of the now closed Phu Thanh Restaurant.
(A couple of their cooks transferred over from Phu Thanh actually.
)  Since then, I've been here about 4-5 times a month.
In my opinion, they're one of the better Vietnamese restaurants in the valley.
Their services has gotten a lot better, they're much faster now, and the interior have also improved quite a bit since they first opened.
Because I love Vietnamese food oh so much, I typically order different items on their menu to satisfy my cravings.
Some dishes are good, like their #21-hoanh thanh soup and their #34-bun thit nuong, some are OK.
I guess you'll just have to go there and give them a try.

